examples.en: The disease is easy to treat if diagnosed early.
The illness was diagnosed as mumps.
She was diagnosed with breast cancer.
She was diagnosed with terminal cancer.
She has been diagnosed with breast cancer.
Joanna was diagnosed as having brittle bones.
The disease is diagnosed most often in children.
The psychiatrist diagnosed the patient as neurotic.
Matthew was wrongly diagnosed as having a brain tumour.
People dropped like flies within weeks of being diagnosed.
Thousands of new cases have been diagnosed in the past year.
Joe struggled in school before he was diagnosed as dyslexic.
Her husband was diagnosed with a terminal illness. (=doctors found that her husband had a terminal illness)
